org.jlibsedml.execution

Class AbstractSedmlExecutor

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jlibsedml.execution.AbstractSedmlExecutor

  • public abstract class AbstractSedmlExecutor
extends Object
    Basis of framework for executing SED-ML. If the SED-ML document has errors, it is possible, but unlikely that the execution of a SED-ML task will occur successfully. Therefore clients should call doc.validate() and check for errors before using this class.

    To use this class clients should subclass and implement the abstract methods:

    • IRawSedmlSimulationResults executeSimulation(String model, UniformTimeCourse simConfig);
    • protected abstract boolean canExecuteSimulation(final Simulation sim);
    • protected abstract boolean supportsLanguage(String language);
    Subclasses should accept a SedML object and an Output object as arguments.

    To run a simulation, call: public final Map runSimulations (); The returned Map can be used within a SedMLResultsProcesser2 object to obtain processed results.

    Author:
    radams

      • executeSimulation

        protected abstract IRawSedmlSimulationResults executeSimulation(String model,
                                                                UniformTimeCourse simConfig)
        Implementing subclasses should run the simulation in this method. If the simulation fails then this should be logged by using the method: 
          protected final  void addStatus(ExecutionStatusElement statusItem)
        and returning null. If execution is successful, then a non-null IRawSedmlSimulationResults object should be returned.
        Parameters:
        model - A String of the XML of the model to simulate.
        simConfig - The simulation configuration
        Returns:
        An object which implements IRawSedmlSimulationResults which will then be processed.

      • getSimulatableTasks

        public List<AbstractTask> getSimulatableTasks()
        Gets a subset of the list of Tasks contained in the supplied model, based on whether the platform can simulate them or not.
        Returns:
        A non-null but possibly empty List of tasks which can be simulated. This decision is made on the basis of Kisao IDs.
